23 likes, 0 comments - afrasiabank on June 4, 2021: "𝐀 𝐠𝐫𝐚𝐭𝐞𝐟𝐮𝐥 𝐭𝐫𝐢𝐛𝐮𝐭𝐞 𝐭𝐨 𝐥𝐚𝐭𝐞 𝐇𝐨𝐧𝐨𝐫𝐚𝐛𝐥𝐞 𝐒𝐢𝐫 𝐀𝐧𝐞𝐫𝐨𝐨𝐝 𝐉𝐮𝐠𝐧𝐚𝐮𝐭𝐡, 𝐆𝐂𝐒𝐊, 𝐊𝐂𝐌𝐆, 𝐐𝐂, 𝐏𝐂
As a humble Mauritian, we honour today the life of purpose led by the Father of Mauritius’s economic miracle. Honorable Sir Anerood Jugnauth has played an instrumental role in the remarkable progress of our Island, having driven our national development whilst positioning the Island on the regional front as well as spotlighting Mauritius on renowned international podiums. Whilst he sets off on his last voyage today, we condole with all Mauritians and pay tribute to the commendable achievements of a Leader who’s left behind a legacy that will last for decades to come.".
